libxr
------------------------------------------
Libxr is a library that allows for rapid implementation of RPC clients and
servers in C.

Libxr features:
  - Multiple RPC transports. (XML-RPC and JSON-RPC)
  - RPC interface description language (XDL)
  - Persistent connections over HTTP/1.1
  - Server session support for non-persistent connections
  - Multi-platform support (Linux, Windows, ...)
  - TLSv1 using GNUTLS

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.25-1
  gettext-0.18.1.1-2
  libffi-devel-3.0.13-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.36.4-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.36.4-1
  libiconv-1.14-2
  libjson-c-devel-0.11-1
  liblzma-devel-5.0.2_20110517-1
  libpcre-devel-8.33-1
  libxml2-2.9.1-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.1-1
  libxr-devel-2.0.0-1bl1
  libxr2-2.0.0-1bl1
  zlib-devel-1.2.8-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cygport-0.13.0-1
  gcc-core-4.7.3-1
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/megous/libxr

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/megous/libxr/archive/2.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libxr-2.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libxr-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxr-2.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxr-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxr2-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxr-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

